result.execSummary:
The defendant was charged with both OWI (3rd) and Operating w/ PAC (3rd). The defendant was found guilty of OWI (3rd) and the other charge, Operating w/ PAC (3rd) was dismissed by the court.

  • Nicholas L Gadzinski was found guilty of OWI (3rd), an unclassified misdemeanor, Wisconsin Statutes 346.63(1)(a).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Nicholas L Gadzinski in court, in custody, with attorney Amber K. Rumpf.   Kristi J Gordon appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Defendant enters a guilty plea as to count 2 and count 1 is dismissed and read-in. Count 3 is dismissed outright. Court imposed the following sentence:

  The defendant was sentenced to the following:

JAIL:  180 days consecutive 16CF469, (Credit - 136 DAYS).  

FINE: $1544.00 (to be paid as a condition of probation on file 16CF469)

DNA SURCHARGE:  $200.00, to be paid at $/month consecutive to payment of fine or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of surcharge.

BLOOD DRAW FEE:  $35.00 paid through Waukesha County Circuit Court to be forward to City of Waukesha Police Department or to be converted to a civil judgment for non payment of fee.

D/L REVOCATION: 24 months;

IGNITION INTERLOCK: 24 months;

Attendance at a Victim Impact Panel during his probation period on 16CF469
